data.enText: one of various types of grass that produce grains that can be eaten or are used to make flour or bread. Wheat , barley and rye are all cereals .
the grain produced by cereal crops

data.chText: （常加牛奶作早餐用的）谷类食物
data.enText: food made from the grain of cereals , often eaten for breakfast with milk

simple_means.memory_skill: cere 谷 + al 物 → 谷物

means: (常加牛奶作早餐用的)谷类食物

tr: a breakfast food prepared from grain
foodstuff prepared from the starchy grains of cereal grasses
grass whose starchy grains are used as food: wheat
made of grain or relating to grain or the plants that produce it

value.def: Cereal or breakfast cereal is a food made from grain. It is mixed with milk and eaten for breakfast.

example.ex: I have a bowl of cereal every morning.
example.tran: 我每天早上喝一碗麦片。

value.tran: (拌以牛奶作早餐的)谷类食品，麦片

value.def: Cereals are plants such as wheat, corn, or rice that produce grain.

example.ex: ...the rich cereal-growing districts of the Paris Basin.
example.tran: 巴黎盆地盛产谷物的地区

meanings.td: 表形容词，“…的，具有…性质的”
